      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SING FOR PEACE (2) hasn't been over the obstacles since finishing second at Ballarat in a hurdle on August 17. The latest effort saw him clock in fifth over 2025m on the flat at Cranbourne. Has had three hurdle trials since and is poised to make a successful return to jumping. FIERCE FLIGHT (3) first up from a spell today and has been switched from the NZ stable. He was heavily bet winning a Te Aroha Maiden hurdle when last seen and Pateman sticks from his latest trials. Has ability and looks ready to go. FABALOT (1) resumes and has switched to the Jackson yard. He's a seasoned jumper who has trialled well for his return. Is a clear top weight but can manage that and is likely to go well.  MR LINCOLN (4) resumes and was last seen on the flat in the 4600m Jericho Cup. Won a Ballarat Maiden hurdle last preparation, but prepared to risk him fresh.",
